  "text": "Excitatory postsynaptic currents (EPSCs) at climbing fi ber synapses are largely mediated by the activation of AMPA receptors (Konnerth et al., 1990; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ) that contain GluR2 subunits and are therefore not permeable to calcium [CITATION_3] . In the following, we will focus on two additional types of glutamate receptors, whose contribution to climbing fi ber signaling (and potential role in calcium signaling) has only recently been fully appreciated: N-methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA) receptors and metabotropic glutamate receptors.",
